headline: 3 Reasons to Sell COO and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Over the past six months, CooperCompanies has been a great trade, beating the S&P 500 by 5.9%. Its stock price has climbed to $82.42, representing a healthy 19.9% increase. This was partly due to its solid quarterly results, and the performance may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
